All Classes

  • All Classes Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AddDocumentCommand
    The class extends Command and lists the contents the catalog.
    Catalog
    The Catalog class implements Serializable in order to convert the state of the objects into byte streams.
    Command
    An abstarct class which new classes will extend in order to create various commands, each having a certain purpose for a user when he will insert a command by its name.
    CommandNotFoundException
    Extends the Exception class in order to create a new exception for the moment a command inserted by the user is not recognized
    CouldntFindInCatalogException
    Extends the Exception class in order to create a new exception for warning the user the catalog doesn't contain a specified document.
    Document
    The Document class implements Serializable in order to allow Catalog to serialize its content (the documents array).
    DuplicateDocumentException
    Extends the Exception class in order to create a new exception for displaying that the catalog already contains the specified document and it would be a duplicate.
    ExternalDocument
    An external file which will be added into the catalog.
    InexistentFileException
    Extends the Exception class in order to create a new exception for displaying that the specified file doesn't exist locally.
    InvalidNumberOfArgumentsException
    Extends the Exception class in order to create a new exception for reminding the user that the command needs more or fewer arguments.
    ListCommand
    The class extends Command and lists the contents the catalog.
    LoadCommand
    The class extends Command and loads an existing catalog previously saved as a file.
    LocalDocument
    A file stored locally which wil be added into a catalog.
    Main  
    NewCatalogCommand
    The class extends Command and creates a new object Catalog with a specified name on which the user make actions.
    NullCatalogException
    Extends the Exception class in order to create a new exception for warning the user that he didn't create a new catalog nor did he load one.
    ReportHtmlCommand
    The class extends Command and creates a report html file with specifications regarding the catalog.
    SaveCommand
    The class extends Command and saves a Catalog object as a local file.
    Shell
    A class able to represent a shell with a list of commands
    ViewCommand
    The class extends Command and opens the specified file found inside the Catalog.
